                                    <li> During @Spell("Beacon of Virtue"), you should never spend @Spell("Infusion of Light") on  @Spell("Judgment") if you can avoid it since it does not transfer any healing through the Beacons. You should instead spend your procs on @Spell("Flash of Light"), or @Spell("Holy Light") if you can afford it.</li>
                                    <li> @Spell("Eternal Flame") or @Spell("Light of Dawn")? - @Spell("Eternal Flame") will be your default option in both Raid and Mythic+. In Raid, @Spell("Light of Dawn") should be used when you don't have a good target for @Spell("Eternal Flame"). In Mythic+ you will practically never use @Spell("Light of Dawn").</li>
                                    <li> @Spell("Beacon of Virtue") - You should prioritize @Spell("Eternal Flame") during @Spell("Beacon of Virtue") because it transfers more healing to Beacons.When @Spell("Beacon of Virtue") is not active, @Spell("Light of Dawn") does more healing, so in Raids you can prioritize it if you do not need spot healing.</li>
