            			<section id="single-button-rotation">
				<h2 class="section-header">
					<img src="/images/SpellIcons/Holy Shock.jpg" alt="Trinkets Icon" class="section-icon">
					IS THE SINGLE BUTTON ROTATION ASSISTANT GOOD FOR HOLY PALADIN?
				</h2>

                <div class="single-button-rotation">
                    <p>
                        For healers, the rotation assistant only uses DPS abilities. It will not use any healing spells, and it will not target your allies in any way. The rotation assistant is therefore not useful for us, and if you want to use the Single Button Assistant on your Paladin, you are better of playing Retribution so you at least do some actual damage.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Rotation Assist Losses for Holy Paladin</h3>
                    <p>
                        Because the Rotation Assistant does not use healing spells, it does not use  Holy Shock even though it is one of our best DPS abilities. It also does not use Holy Power, not even to cast  Shield of the Righteous. Combining these two factors means the Rotation Assistant often has giant gaps between its spell usage as it frequently has no available spell to cast, and as such it is a huge DPS loss to use it.
                    </p>   
                    <h3>Holy Paladin DPS Spells and Cooldowns Not Used by Rotation Assist</h3>
                    <p>
                        Besides not using any healing spells, it also does not use any sort of cooldowns either, so when using both Assisted Highlight and Single-Button Assistant to deal damage as a Holy Paladin, you will still need to use the following spells and cooldowns manually.
                    </p>                    
                    <ul>
                        <li> @Spell("Avenging Wrath")</li>
                            <li> @Spell("Divine Toll")</li>
                            <li> All the different Blessings from @Spell("Blessing of Summer")</li>
                            <li> @Spell("Holy Prism")</li>
                            <li> @Spell("Holy Shock")</li>
                            <li> @Spell("Spend Holy Power") on @Spell("Shield of the Righteous")</li>
                    </ul>                  
